    {"id": "ko_cp_036", "levels": [{"front": "To go", "back": "가다", "romanized": "gada", "grammarNote": "Korean verbs come at the end of the sentence. 'Gada' (가다, to go) becomes '가요' (gayo) in polite present tense. Destination uses '에' (e): '슈퍼에 가요' = I'm going to the supermarket. '오다' (oda, to come) is the opposite direction."}, {"front": "I'm going to the supermarket.", "back": "슈퍼마켓에 가요.", "romanized": "syupeomakete gayo", "literal": "Supermarket to go."}]},
