    {"id": "ko_cp_051", "levels": [{"front": "In", "back": "안에 / ~에", "romanized": "ane / ~e", "grammarNote": "Korean location expressions use postpositions (after the noun). Key ones: '안에' (ane, inside/in), '위에' (wie, on top), '아래에' (araee, under), '옆에' (yeope, next to), '앞에' (ape, in front), '뒤에' (dwie, behind). Existence uses '있어요' (isseoyo)."}, {"front": "The keys are in the bag.", "back": "열쇠가 가방 안에 있어요.", "romanized": "yeolsoega gabang ane isseoyo", "literal": "Keys [subj] bag inside at is."}]},
